summary: This document is an email chain from January 21, 2020, discussing logistical preparations for foreign travel by an individual associated with the 'Epstein team'. The correspondence involves coordinating with the Executive Office for United States Attorneys (EOUSA) to provide a passport, itinerary, airfare booking, and a signed travel authorization memo.

events.title: Foreign Travel Coordination
events.description: Email correspondence regarding the logistical process for booking foreign travel, including obtaining a passport, itinerary, airfare, and a signed travel authorization memo from the 'Epstein team' in coordination with EOUSA.

keyFacts: The email references an 'Epstein team' working on travel arrangements in January 2020.
Coordination for the travel involves the Executive Office for United States Attorneys (EOUSA), which has received a passport and is requesting a corresponding itinerary and travel authorization.
The travel process requires a signed travel memo, airfare booking, and EOUSA approval, with no guarantee the passport will be ready in time.
The document is a logistical email chain, not a legal filing or transcript, showing administrative planning post-Epstein's death.
All sender, recipient, and cc fields in the email are redacted or empty in the provided text.
